  "dateStart": "2025-09-02",
  "description": "<p>This single degree program is composed of a selected combination of courses from the <a href=\"#/experiences/rJeiHV5iV\">School of Earth and Ocean Sciences</a> and the <a href=\"#/experiences/r1DAk4co4\">Department of Chemistry</a>. Students complete this program in the <a href=\"#/experiences/rJwWOW5oN\">Faculty of Science</a> and must consult the <a href=\"#/experiences/BylJ9-cs4\">Faculty Program Requirements</a>. The program introduces students to the field of geochemistry while providing a firm basis in the principles of chemistry.</p>",
  "id": "6778746b660e11c9a58a2cad",
  "pid": "Hy6Ia7CGN",
  "programNotes": "<h4>Program notes</h4> <ul> <li>Students with Chemistry 11 and Pre-Calculus 12 or equivalents must take CHEM <a href=\"#/courses/Hk0p0w6XV\">091</a> before enrolling in CHEM <a href=\"#/courses/r11A0D6XN\">102</a>. Students with Chemistry 12 and Pre-Calculus 12 or equivalents should not take CHEM <a href=\"#/courses/Hk0p0w6XV\">091</a>.</li> <li>Completion of a field school as an EOS elective is recommended. EOS <a href=\"#/courses/Sy8n7_a74\">300</a> requires that EOS <a href=\"#/courses/H1V3XuTX4\">202</a> be taken as an elective. EOS <a href=\"#/courses/S1oIB9G_N\">401</a> requires three of EOS <a href=\"#/courses/BkdhQ_pQV\">311</a>, <a href=\"#/courses/Syuhm_TmE\">312</a>, <a href=\"#/courses/B1dh7_T7V\">313</a> or (<a href=\"#/courses/S1tn7d6QE\">314</a> or <a href=\"#/courses/ryWamu67N\">431</a>) be taken as electives.</li> <li>Most 400-level EOS classes are offered in alternate years. A schedule of when each class is offered is available on the School of Earth and Ocean Sciences website.</li> </ul>",
